title: 3D Printing Bagpipes in Seattle
text:
Anyone here have a Form 2 or 3? The shop space I rent time in closed due to the pandemic, and I was in the middle of developing a number of new and historical Celtic woodwinds, including a vintage pennywhistle design that was one or two prints away from being finalized. I'm going nuts having four years of work come to a screeching halt, and wondered whether anyone would be up for running some prints. Obviously, I'd pay for material costs and shipping, if you'd prefer not to meet in person.

I know many people are using their printers to create personal protective equipment for healthcare workers at this time, so I would of course wait until the need for gear is lower. I haven't heard from my friend at Harborview so I'm not sure whether they're still in dire straights or not.
